<br>
A hammer user would be insane to spec to 50.  He/She would have less than a 5% chance to use his/her lvl 50 style.  It isn't as bad in Axe and Sword, but there are still styles that simply won't be used.  I don't even bother, never have, with having Frost Cut on my quickbar.  I'm sure I won't bother with Niord's furry either.<br>
<br>
I read your 1.60 report hoping to see that mentioned, but it wasn't there.  I was just curious as to why?<br>
<br>
Also, I wanted to suggest something.  Would it be balanceable and conceivable that Skalds could have a different ability in their singing that goes like this.  If we sing a song for a certain amount of time, our group mates would take up the song on their own, allowing us to sing something else, if even for a short time.  This would not go outside Norse mythology and history.  I am a history major at Indiana University and have taken a Norse Mythology/History course.  Otherwise, even if we do get additions to our spell line, we won't be using them all that much, because our groups are still going to want Speed.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp.<br>
<br>
Edge<br>
<br>
Cuhlbey 35 Skald~Merlin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gisborne>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 287<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/1/03 11:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=597.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Roseanne</span><hr size=1> Hammer/Sword/Axe spec is shared by other midgard classes. The styles are the same for all of them.<br>
